        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:52PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Todd Mission, or 8 miles west of Pinehurst, moving northwest at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pinehurst, Magnolia, Todd Mission, and Plantersville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
